  "prompt": "[SPOILER] Why didn't Jon ask Melisandre to resurrect Rickon after he died in the war?",
  "response": "There are a few reasons why Jon likely didn't ask Melisandre to resurrect Rickon:\n\n1. Jon had already seen the consequences of resurrection through Beric Dondarrion, who lost parts of his memory and humanity each time he was brought back.\n\n2. Melisandre's resurrection of Jon was a unique and difficult event, and she seemed unsure of her ability to consistently perform this magic.\n\n3. Rickon's death was sudden and traumatic, and Jon was deeply grieving, which might have made him less rational about magical solutions.\n\n4. By the time of Rickon's death, Jon had become more skeptical of magical interventions after his own resurrection experience.\n\nAlso, from a narrative perspective, Rickon's death served to heighten the emotional stakes of the Battle of the Bastards and demonstrate the brutal nature of the conflict.",
